scenario:
No violation in the shown fragment: metal_generic_dev_open calls metal_generic_dev_sys_open(dev), which is a different function name. There is no evidence here that metal_generic_dev_open calls itself directly. This is not a Rule 17.2 violation unless metal_generic_dev_sys_open (or some chain of calls it triggers) calls back into metal_generic_dev_open (or creates a call cycle). A concrete violation scenario would be if metal_generic_dev_sys_open were implemented like:

int metal_generic_dev_sys_open(struct metal_device *dev) {
    /* ... */
    return metal_generic_dev_open(dev->bus, dev->name, /*...*/);
}

which would create indirect recursion and thus violate Rule 17.2.
